{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":44,"text":"Is E.T. out there?"},{"time":1037,"text":"Well, I work at the SETI Institute."},{"time":4016,"text":"That's almost my name. SETI:"},{"time":5251,"text":"Search for Extraterrestrial Intelligence."},{"time":7658,"text":"In other words, I look for aliens,"},{"time":9277,"text":"and when I tell people that at a cocktail party, they usually"},{"time":12945,"text":"look at me with a mildly incredulous look on their face."},{"time":15706,"text":"I try to keep my own face somewhat dispassionate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":18039,"text":"Now, a lot of people think that this is kind of idealistic,"},{"time":20799,"text":"ridiculous, maybe even hopeless,"},{"time":23049,"text":"but I just want to talk to you a little bit about why I think"},{"time":26754,"text":"that the job I have is actually a privilege, okay,"},{"time":30568,"text":"and give you a little bit of the motivation for my getting into"},{"time":32666,"text":"this line of work, if that's what you call it."},{"time":35021,"text":"This thing — whoops, can we go back?"},{"time":38029,"text":"Hello, come in, Earth."},{"time":40728,"text":"There we go. All right."}]},{"cues":[{"time":42079,"text":"This is the Owens Valley Radio Observatory"},{"time":44072,"text":"behind the Sierra Nevadas, and in 1968,"},{"time":47508,"text":"I was working there collecting data for my thesis."},{"time":50417,"text":"Now, it's kinda lonely, it's kinda tedious, just collecting data,"},{"time":53758,"text":"so I would amuse myself by taking photos at night"},{"time":56291,"text":"of the telescopes or even of myself,"},{"time":59052,"text":"because, you know, at night, I would be the only hominid"},{"time":64286,"text":"within about 30 miles."},{"time":66034,"text":"So here are pictures of myself."},{"time":68043,"text":"The observatory had just acquired a new book,"},{"time":71631,"text":"written by a Russian cosmologist"},{"time":73381,"text":"by the name of Joseph Shklovsky, and then expanded"},{"time":76999,"text":"and translated and edited by a little-known"},{"time":79452,"text":"Cornell astronomer by the name of Carl Sagan."}]},{"cues":[{"time":82061,"text":"And I remember reading that book,"},{"time":84058,"text":"and at 3 in the morning I was reading this book"},{"time":86066,"text":"and it was explaining how the antennas I was using"},{"time":88759,"text":"to measure the spins of galaxies could also be used"},{"time":93706,"text":"to communicate, to send bits of information"},{"time":96018,"text":"from one star system to another."},{"time":98610,"text":"Now, at 3 o'clock in the morning when you're all alone,"},{"time":100078,"text":"haven't had much sleep, that was a very romantic idea,"},{"time":103009,"text":"but it was that idea -- the fact that you could in fact"},{"time":106898,"text":"prove that there's somebody out there"},{"time":108382,"text":"just using this same technology --"},{"time":111098,"text":"that appealed to me so much that 20 years later I took a job"},{"time":113328,"text":"at the SETI Institute. Now, I have to say"},{"time":115301,"text":"that my memory is notoriously porous, and I've often"},{"time":119751,"text":"wondered whether there was any truth in this story,"},{"time":121584,"text":"or I was just, you know, misremembering something,"},{"time":123088,"text":"but I recently just blew up this old negative of mine,"},{"time":125836,"text":"and sure enough, there you can see"},{"time":127435,"text":"the Shklovsky and Sagan book underneath that"},{"time":129546,"text":"analog calculating device."},{"time":132023,"text":"So it was true."}]},{"cues":[{"time":132926,"text":"All right. Now, the idea for doing this, it wasn't very old"},{"time":135367,"text":"at the time that I made that photo."},{"time":137031,"text":"The idea dates from 1960, when a young astronomer"},{"time":140509,"text":"by the name of Frank Drake used this antenna"},{"time":143005,"text":"in West Virginia, pointed it at a couple of nearby stars"},{"time":146615,"text":"in the hopes of eavesdropping on E.T."},{"time":150004,"text":"Now, Frank didn't hear anything."},{"time":151600,"text":"Actually he did, but it turned out to be the U.S. Air Force,"},{"time":154009,"text":"which doesn't count as extraterrestrial intelligence."},{"time":156974,"text":"But Drake's idea here became very popular"},{"time":159740,"text":"because it was very appealing — and I'll get back to that —"},{"time":162197,"text":"and on the basis of this experiment, which didn't succeed,"},{"time":165613,"text":"we have been doing SETI ever since,"},{"time":167468,"text":"not continuously, but ever since."}]},{"cues":[{"time":169502,"text":"We still haven't heard anything."},{"time":171388,"text":"We still haven't heard anything."},{"time":173066,"text":"In fact, we don't know about any life beyond Earth,"},{"time":174859,"text":"but I'm going to suggest to you that that's going to change"},{"time":177659,"text":"rather soon, and part of the reason, in fact,"},{"time":180028,"text":"the majority of the reason why I think that's going to change"},{"time":182803,"text":"is that the equipment's getting better."},{"time":184068,"text":"This is the Allen Telescope Array, about 350 miles"},{"time":187005,"text":"from whatever seat you're in right now."},{"time":189021,"text":"This is something that we're using today"},{"time":191026,"text":"to search for E.T., and the electronics have gotten"},{"time":193030,"text":"very much better too."},{"time":194500,"text":"This is Frank Drake's electronics in 1960."},{"time":197026,"text":"This is the Allen Telescope Array electronics today."},{"time":199047,"text":"Some pundit with too much time on his hands"},{"time":202536,"text":"has reckoned that the new experiments are approximately"},{"time":205543,"text":"100 trillion times better than they were in 1960,"},{"time":210038,"text":"100 trillion times better."},{"time":211534,"text":"That's a degree of an improvement that would look good"},{"time":213623,"text":"on your report card, okay?"},{"time":216030,"text":"But something that's not appreciated by the public is,"},{"time":218664,"text":"in fact, that the experiment continues to get better,"},{"time":221389,"text":"and, consequently, tends to get faster."},{"time":224037,"text":"This is a little plot, and every time you show a plot,"},{"time":225726,"text":"you lose 10 percent of the audience."},{"time":227364,"text":"I have 12 of these. (Laughter)"},{"time":229673,"text":"But what I plotted here is just some metric"},{"time":234093,"text":"that shows how fast we're searching."},{"time":236647,"text":"In other words, we're looking for a needle in a haystack."},{"time":238755,"text":"We know how big the haystack is. It's the galaxy."},{"time":241042,"text":"But we're going through the haystack no longer"},{"time":243753,"text":"with a teaspoon but with a skip loader,"},{"time":246045,"text":"because of this increase in speed."},{"time":248016,"text":"In fact, those of you who are still conscious"},{"time":249451,"text":"and mathematically competent,"},{"time":252011,"text":"will note that this is a semi-log plot."},{"time":254089,"text":"In other words, the rate of increase is exponential."},{"time":258481,"text":"It's exponentially improving. Now, exponential is an"},{"time":261214,"text":"overworked word. You hear it on the media all the time."},{"time":263533,"text":"They don't really know what exponential means,"},{"time":265070,"text":"but this is exponential."},{"time":267081,"text":"In fact, it's doubling every 18 months, and, of course,"},{"time":270001,"text":"every card-carrying member of the digerati knows"},{"time":272005,"text":"that that's Moore's Law."}]},{"cues":[{"time":273497,"text":"So this means that over the course of the next"},{"time":276098,"text":"two dozen years, we'll be able to look at a million star systems,"},{"time":280010,"text":"a million star systems, looking for signals"},{"time":282038,"text":"that would prove somebody's out there."},{"time":283547,"text":"Well, a million star systems, is that interesting?"},{"time":286045,"text":"I mean, how many of those star systems have planets?"},{"time":289059,"text":"And the facts are, we didn't know the answer to that"},{"time":291204,"text":"even as recently as 15 years ago, and in fact, we really"},{"time":293978,"text":"didn't know it even as recently as six months ago."},{"time":296501,"text":"But now we do. Recent results suggest"},{"time":299379,"text":"that virtually every star has planets, and more than one."},{"time":303018,"text":"They're like, you know, kittens. You get a litter."},{"time":306344,"text":"You don't get one kitten. You get a bunch."},{"time":308084,"text":"So in fact, this is a pretty accurate estimate"},{"time":311018,"text":"of the number of planets in our galaxy,"},{"time":315014,"text":"just in our galaxy, by the way,"},{"time":317041,"text":"and I remind the non-astronomy majors among you"},{"time":319811,"text":"that our galaxy is only one of 100 billion"},{"time":322056,"text":"that we can see with our telescopes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":324040,"text":"That's a lot of real estate, but of course,"},{"time":325563,"text":"most of these planets are going to be kind of worthless,"},{"time":327472,"text":"like, you know, Mercury, or Neptune."},{"time":329564,"text":"Neptune's probably not very big in your life."},{"time":331654,"text":"So the question is, what fraction of these planets"},{"time":336001,"text":"are actually suitable for life?"},{"time":337683,"text":"We don't know the answer to that either,"},{"time":339088,"text":"but we will learn that answer this year, thanks to"},{"time":341326,"text":"NASA's Kepler Space Telescope,"},{"time":343082,"text":"and in fact, the smart money, which is to say the people who work on this project,"},{"time":347104,"text":"the smart money is suggesting that the fraction of planets"},{"time":350533,"text":"that might be suitable for life is maybe one in a thousand,"},{"time":354569,"text":"one in a hundred, something like that."},{"time":357876,"text":"Well, even taking the pessimistic estimate, that it's"},{"time":360016,"text":"one in a thousand, that means that there are"},{"time":363127,"text":"at least a billion cousins of the Earth"},{"time":365656,"text":"just in our own galaxy."},{"time":367383,"text":"Okay, now I've given you a lot of numbers here,"},{"time":369636,"text":"but they're mostly big numbers, okay, so, you know,"},{"time":373562,"text":"keep that in mind. There's plenty of real estate,"},{"time":376041,"text":"plenty of real estate in the universe,"},{"time":378054,"text":"and if we're the only bit of real estate in which there's"},{"time":381003,"text":"some interesting occupants, that makes you a miracle,"},{"time":384038,"text":"and I know you like to think you're a miracle,"},{"time":386719,"text":"but if you do science, you learn rather quickly that"},{"time":388629,"text":"every time you think you're a miracle, you're wrong,"},{"time":390512,"text":"so probably not the case."}]},{"cues":[{"time":393040,"text":"All right, so the bottom line is this:"},{"time":395091,"text":"Because of the increase in speed, and because of the"},{"time":398054,"text":"vast amount of habitable real estate in the cosmos, I figure"},{"time":403005,"text":"we're going to pick up a signal within two dozen years."},{"time":405050,"text":"And I feel strongly enough about that to make a bet with you:"},{"time":408021,"text":"Either we're going to find E.T. in the next two dozen years,"},{"time":410458,"text":"or I'll buy you a cup of coffee."},{"time":414076,"text":"So that's not so bad. I mean, even with two dozen years,"},{"time":416710,"text":"you open up your browser and there's news of a signal,"},{"time":418569,"text":"or you get a cup of coffee."},{"time":420320,"text":"Now, let me tell you about some aspect of this that"},{"time":424293,"text":"people don't think about, and that is,"},{"time":426331,"text":"what happens? Suppose that what I say is true."},{"time":430039,"text":"I mean, who knows, but suppose it happens."},{"time":432404,"text":"Suppose some time in the next two dozen years"},{"time":433891,"text":"we pick up a faint line that tells us"},{"time":436068,"text":"we have some cosmic company."},{"time":437756,"text":"What is the effect? What's the consequence?"},{"time":440051,"text":"Now, I might be at ground zero for this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":442015,"text":"I happen to know what the consequence for me would be,"},{"time":443836,"text":"because we've had false alarms. This is 1997,"},{"time":446760,"text":"and this is a photo I made at about 3 o'clock in the morning"},{"time":449044,"text":"in Mountain View here, when we were watching"},{"time":451053,"text":"the computer monitors because we had picked up a signal"},{"time":453368,"text":"that we thought, \"This is the real deal.\" All right?"},{"time":456446,"text":"And I kept waiting for the Men in Black to show up. Right?"},{"time":459814,"text":"I kept waiting for -- I kept waiting for my mom to call,"},{"time":464017,"text":"somebody to call, the government to call. Nobody called."},{"time":467021,"text":"Nobody called. I was so nervous"},{"time":470191,"text":"that I couldn't sit down. I just wandered around"},{"time":472015,"text":"taking photos like this one, just for something to do."},{"time":475005,"text":"Well, at 9:30 in the morning, with my head down"},{"time":477039,"text":"on my desk because I obviously hadn't slept all night,"},{"time":479069,"text":"the phone rings and it's The New York Times."},{"time":481406,"text":"And I think there's a lesson in that, and that lesson is"},{"time":484032,"text":"that if we pick up a signal, the media, the media will be on it"},{"time":487012,"text":"faster than a weasel on ball bearings. It's going to be fast."},{"time":491346,"text":"You can be sure of that. No secrecy."},{"time":493024,"text":"That's what happens to me. It kind of ruins my whole week,"},{"time":496007,"text":"because whatever I've got planned that week is kind of out the window."}]},{"cues":[{"time":498630,"text":"But what about you? What's it going to do to you?"},{"time":501050,"text":"And the answer is that we don't know the answer."},{"time":503057,"text":"We don't know what that's going to do to you,"},{"time":503942,"text":"not in the long term, and not even very much in the short term."},{"time":507066,"text":"I mean, that would be a bit like"},{"time":509894,"text":"asking Chris Columbus in 1491, \"Hey Chris,"},{"time":513000,"text":"you know, what happens if it turns out that there's a"},{"time":515014,"text":"continent between here and Japan, where you're sailing to,"},{"time":518550,"text":"what will be the consequences for humanity"},{"time":521325,"text":"if that turns out to be the case?\""},{"time":523071,"text":"And I think Chris would probably offer you some answer"},{"time":525301,"text":"that you might not have understood, but it probably"},{"time":528012,"text":"wouldn't have been right, and I think that to predict"},{"time":530846,"text":"what finding E.T.'s going to mean,"},{"time":532605,"text":"we can't predict that either."},{"time":533685,"text":"But here are a couple things I can say."},{"time":535307,"text":"To begin with, it's going to be a society that's way in advance of our own."},{"time":539464,"text":"You're not going to hear from alien Neanderthals."},{"time":541088,"text":"They're not building transmitters."},{"time":542378,"text":"They're going to be ahead of us, maybe by a few thousand"},{"time":544304,"text":"years, maybe by a few millions years, but substantially"},{"time":547371,"text":"ahead of us, and that means, if you can understand"},{"time":549600,"text":"anything that they're going to say, then you might be able"},{"time":553386,"text":"to short-circuit history by getting information from a society"},{"time":556476,"text":"that's way beyond our own."},{"time":558050,"text":"Now, you might find that a bit hyperbolic, and maybe it is,"},{"time":561001,"text":"but nonetheless, it's conceivable that this will happen,"},{"time":563654,"text":"and, you know, you could consider this like, I don't know,"},{"time":566027,"text":"giving Julius Caesar English lessons and the key"},{"time":568496,"text":"to the library of Congress."},{"time":569603,"text":"It would change his day, all right?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":572058,"text":"That's one thing. Another thing that's for sure"},{"time":574053,"text":"going to happen is that it will calibrate us."},{"time":577553,"text":"We will know that we're not that miracle, right,"},{"time":581491,"text":"that we're just another duck in a row,"},{"time":583053,"text":"we're not the only kids on the block, and I think that that's"},{"time":585048,"text":"philosophically a very profound thing to learn."},{"time":588002,"text":"We're not a miracle, okay?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":591103,"text":"The third thing that it might tell you is somewhat vague,"},{"time":594402,"text":"but I think interesting and important,"},{"time":596525,"text":"and that is, if you find a signal coming from a more"},{"time":598630,"text":"advanced society, because they will be,"},{"time":600861,"text":"that will tell you something about our own possibilities,"},{"time":603513,"text":"that we're not inevitably doomed to self-destruction."},{"time":608295,"text":"Because they survived their technology,"},{"time":610091,"text":"we could do it too."},{"time":611203,"text":"Normally when you look out into the universe,"},{"time":613094,"text":"you're looking back in time. All right?"},{"time":615555,"text":"That's interesting to cosmologists."},{"time":617594,"text":"But in this sense, you actually can look into the future,"},{"time":621038,"text":"hazily, but you can look into the future."},{"time":623053,"text":"So those are all the sorts of things that would come from a detection."}]},{"cues":[{"time":628590,"text":"Now, let me talk a little bit about something that happens"},{"time":631022,"text":"even in the meantime, and that is,"},{"time":635234,"text":"SETI, I think, is important, because it's exploration, and"},{"time":640012,"text":"it's not only exploration, it's comprehensible exploration."},{"time":642464,"text":"Now, I gotta tell you, I'm always reading books about"},{"time":645329,"text":"explorers. I find exploration very interesting,"},{"time":648044,"text":"Arctic exploration, you know, people like Magellan,"},{"time":651025,"text":"Amundsen, Shackleton, you see Franklin down there,"},{"time":654021,"text":"Scott, all these guys. It's really nifty, exploration."},{"time":657345,"text":"And they're just doing it because they want to explore,"},{"time":659584,"text":"and you might say, \"Oh, that's kind of a frivolous opportunity,\""},{"time":661700,"text":"but that's not frivolous. That's not a frivolous activity,"},{"time":665028,"text":"because, I mean, think of ants."},{"time":667059,"text":"You know, most ants are programmed to follow one another"},{"time":669056,"text":"along in a long line, but there are a couple of ants,"},{"time":671304,"text":"maybe one percent of those ants, that are what they call"},{"time":674000,"text":"pioneer ants, and they're the ones that wander off."},{"time":676175,"text":"They're the ones you find on the kitchen countertop."},{"time":678076,"text":"You gotta get them with your thumb before they"},{"time":680074,"text":"find the sugar or something."},{"time":681658,"text":"But those ants, even though most of them get wiped out,"},{"time":684063,"text":"those ants are the ones that are essential to the survival"},{"time":687355,"text":"of the hive. So exploration is important."}]},{"cues":[{"time":690929,"text":"I also think that exploration is important in terms of"},{"time":694309,"text":"being able to address what I think is a critical"},{"time":699179,"text":"lack in our society, and that is the lack of science literacy,"},{"time":702380,"text":"the lack of the ability to even understand science."},{"time":706023,"text":"Now, look, a lot has been written about the"},{"time":708065,"text":"deplorable state of science literacy in this country."},{"time":711463,"text":"You've heard about it."},{"time":714015,"text":"Well, here's one example, in fact."},{"time":716067,"text":"Polls taken, this poll was taken 10 years ago."},{"time":718386,"text":"It shows like roughly one third of the public thinks"},{"time":720515,"text":"that aliens are not only out there, we're looking for them"},{"time":722479,"text":"out there, but they're here, right?"},{"time":724097,"text":"Sailing the skies in their saucers and occasionally"},{"time":726396,"text":"abducting people for experiments their parents wouldn't approve of."},{"time":729512,"text":"Well, that would be interesting if it was true,"},{"time":732685,"text":"and job security for me, but I don't think the evidence is"},{"time":734564,"text":"very good. That's more, you know, sad than significant."}]},{"cues":[{"time":738036,"text":"But there are other things that people believe"},{"time":740055,"text":"that are significant, like the efficacy of homeopathy,"},{"time":743466,"text":"or that evolution is just, you know, sort of a crazy idea"},{"time":747017,"text":"by scientists without any legs, or, you know, evolution,"},{"time":750048,"text":"all that sort of thing, or global warming."},{"time":752604,"text":"These sorts of ideas don't really have any validity,"},{"time":756005,"text":"that you can't trust the scientists."}]},{"cues":[{"time":758080,"text":"Now, we've got to solve that problem, because that's"},{"time":760323,"text":"a critically important problem, and you might say,"},{"time":764401,"text":"\"Well, okay, how are we gonna solve that problem with SETI?\""},{"time":767030,"text":"Well, let me suggest to you that SETI obviously can't"},{"time":769429,"text":"solve the problem, but it can address the problem."},{"time":771092,"text":"It can address the problem by getting young people"},{"time":774035,"text":"interested in science. Look, science is hard, it"},{"time":777033,"text":"has a reputation of being hard, and the facts are, it is hard,"},{"time":780086,"text":"and that's the result of 400 years of science, right?"},{"time":785021,"text":"I mean, in the 18th century, in the 18th century"},{"time":787500,"text":"you could become an expert on any field of science"},{"time":790090,"text":"in an afternoon by going to a library,"},{"time":793004,"text":"if you could find the library, right?"},{"time":795025,"text":"In the 19th century, if you had a basement lab,"},{"time":798641,"text":"you could make major scientific discoveries"},{"time":801388,"text":"in your own home. Right? Because there was all this"},{"time":803613,"text":"science just lying around waiting for somebody to pick it up."},{"time":806488,"text":"Now, that's not true anymore."},{"time":808081,"text":"Today, you've got to spend years in grad school"},{"time":810509,"text":"and post-doc positions just to figure out what"},{"time":814007,"text":"the important questions are."},{"time":816063,"text":"It's hard. There's no doubt about it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":818058,"text":"And in fact, here's an example: the Higgs boson,"},{"time":820367,"text":"finding the Higgs boson."},{"time":822276,"text":"Ask the next 10 people you see on the streets,"},{"time":824076,"text":"\"Hey, do you think it's worthwhile to spend billions"},{"time":826414,"text":"of Swiss francs looking for the Higgs boson?\""},{"time":829055,"text":"And I bet the answer you're going to get, is,"},{"time":831376,"text":"\"Well, I don't know what the Higgs boson is,"},{"time":833033,"text":"and I don't know if it's important.\""},{"time":834265,"text":"And probably most of the people wouldn't even know"},{"time":836064,"text":"the value of a Swiss franc, okay?"},{"time":838511,"text":"And yet we're spending billions of Swiss francs on this problem."},{"time":841041,"text":"Okay? So that doesn't get people interested in science"},{"time":843194,"text":"because they can't comprehend what it's about."},{"time":845070,"text":"SETI, on the other hand, is really simple."},{"time":846687,"text":"We're going to use these big antennas and we're going to"},{"time":848303,"text":"try to eavesdrop on signals. Everybody can understand that."},{"time":851055,"text":"Yes, technologically, it's very sophisticated,"},{"time":853064,"text":"but everybody gets the idea."}]},{"cues":[{"time":855070,"text":"So that's one thing. The other thing is, it's exciting science."},{"time":859008,"text":"It's exciting because we're naturally interested"},{"time":861422,"text":"in other intelligent beings, and I think that's"},{"time":863647,"text":"part of our hardwiring."},{"time":865071,"text":"I mean, we're hardwired to be interested"},{"time":866631,"text":"in beings that might be, if you will, competitors,"},{"time":869432,"text":"or if you're the romantic sort, possibly even mates. Okay?"},{"time":873015,"text":"I mean, this is analogous to our interest in things that"},{"time":875026,"text":"have big teeth. Right?"},{"time":877047,"text":"We're interested in things that have big teeth, and you"},{"time":878521,"text":"can see the evolutionary value of that, and you can also see"},{"time":881066,"text":"the practical consequences by watching Animal Planet."},{"time":884754,"text":"You notice they make very few programs about gerbils."},{"time":887088,"text":"It's mostly about things that have big teeth."},{"time":889144,"text":"Okay, so we're interested in these sorts of things."},{"time":892091,"text":"And not just us. It's also kids."},{"time":896026,"text":"This allows you to pay it forward by using this subject as a"},{"time":899453,"text":"hook to science, because SETI involves all kinds of science,"},{"time":902685,"text":"obviously biology, obviously astronomy,"},{"time":904675,"text":"but also geology, also chemistry, various scientific"},{"time":908009,"text":"disciplines all can be presented in the guise of,"},{"time":912009,"text":"\"We're looking for E.T.\""},{"time":913338,"text":"So to me this is interesting and important, and in fact,"},{"time":917795,"text":"it's my policy, even though I give a lot of talks to adults,"},{"time":921033,"text":"you give talks to adults, and two days later they're back where they were."},{"time":923701,"text":"But if you give talks to kids, you know,"},{"time":926623,"text":"one in 50 of them, some light bulb goes off, and they think,"},{"time":930775,"text":"\"Gee, I'd never thought of that,\" and then they go,"},{"time":932576,"text":"you know, read a book or a magazine or whatever."},{"time":934368,"text":"They get interested in something."}]},{"cues":[{"time":936050,"text":"Now it's my theory, supported only by anecdotal,"},{"time":941024,"text":"personal anecdotal evidence, but nonetheless,"},{"time":943047,"text":"that kids get interested in something between the ages"},{"time":945520,"text":"of eight and 11. You've got to get them there."},{"time":948056,"text":"So, all right, I give talks to adults, that's fine, but I try"},{"time":950676,"text":"and make 10 percent of the talks that I give,"},{"time":953001,"text":"I try and make those for kids."},{"time":955078,"text":"I remember when a guy came to our high school, actually,"},{"time":958054,"text":"it was actually my junior high school. I was in sixth grade."},{"time":961030,"text":"And he gave some talk. All I remember from it"},{"time":963510,"text":"was one word: electronics."},{"time":965085,"text":"It was like Dustin Hoffman in \"The Graduate,\" right,"},{"time":967646,"text":"when he said \"plastics,\" whatever that means, plastics."},{"time":970044,"text":"All right, so the guy said electronics. I don't remember"},{"time":972039,"text":"anything else. In fact, I don't remember anything"},{"time":974043,"text":"that my sixth grade teacher said all year,"},{"time":976053,"text":"but I remember electronics."},{"time":978067,"text":"And so I got interested in electronics, and you know,"},{"time":980719,"text":"I studied to get my ham license. I was wiring up stuff."},{"time":983044,"text":"Here I am at about 15 or something, doing that sort of stuff."},{"time":986022,"text":"Okay? That had a big effect on me."},{"time":987605,"text":"So that's my point, that you can have a big effect"},{"time":989317,"text":"on these kids."}]},{"cues":[{"time":992033,"text":"In fact, this reminds me, I don't know, a couple years ago"},{"time":995694,"text":"I gave a talk at a school in Palo Alto"},{"time":999020,"text":"where there were about a dozen 11-year-olds"},{"time":1001033,"text":"that had come to this talk."},{"time":1002005,"text":"I had been brought in to talk to these kids for an hour."},{"time":1004521,"text":"Eleven-year-olds, they're all sitting in a little semi-circle"},{"time":1006795,"text":"looking up at me with big eyes, and I started,"},{"time":1009039,"text":"there was a white board behind me, and I started off"},{"time":1010695,"text":"by writing a one with 22 zeroes after it, and I said,"},{"time":1013533,"text":"\"All right, now look, this is the number of stars"},{"time":1015896,"text":"in the visible universe, and this number is so big"},{"time":1018768,"text":"there's not even a name for it.\""},{"time":1022116,"text":"And one of these kids shot up his hand, and he said,"},{"time":1024581,"text":"\"Well, actually there is a name for it."},{"time":1026086,"text":"It's a sextra-quadra-hexa-something or other.\" Right?"},{"time":1029020,"text":"Now, that kid was wrong by four orders of magnitude,"},{"time":1033016,"text":"but there was no doubt about it, these kids were smart."},{"time":1035488,"text":"Okay? So I stopped giving the lecture."},{"time":1037456,"text":"All they wanted to do was ask questions."},{"time":1040039,"text":"In fact, my last comments to these kids, at the end I said,"},{"time":1044031,"text":"\"You know, you kids are smarter"},{"time":1046063,"text":"than the people I work with.\" Now — (Laughter)"},{"time":1051005,"text":"They didn't even care about that."},{"time":1052334,"text":"What they wanted was my email address"},{"time":1055028,"text":"so they could ask me more questions. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1059013,"text":"Let me just say, look, my job is a privilege"},{"time":1062172,"text":"because we're in a special time."},{"time":1063795,"text":"Previous generations couldn't do this experiment at all."},{"time":1066580,"text":"In another generation down the line,"},{"time":1068405,"text":"I think we will have succeeded."},{"time":1070021,"text":"So to me, it is a privilege, and when I look in the mirror,"},{"time":1073502,"text":"the facts are that I really don't see myself."},{"time":1076309,"text":"What I see is the generation behind me."},{"time":1078073,"text":"These are some kids from the Huff School, fourth graders."},{"time":1080099,"text":"I talked there, what, two weeks ago, something like that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1083044,"text":"I think that if you can instill some interest in science"},{"time":1087654,"text":"and how it works, well, that's a payoff"},{"time":1090613,"text":"beyond easy measure. Thank you very much."},{"time":1093056,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}